---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/sections/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../components/sections/Footer.astro";

const lastUpdated = "May 14, 2026";
const effectiveDate = "May 14, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service — BotPilot"
  description="The terms that govern your use of BotPilot for Android and BotPilot Creator for iOS."
  canonical="https://botpilot.org/terms"
>
  <Navbar />

  <main class="legal">
    <div class="legal-bg">
      <div class="legal-orb legal-orb1"></div>
      <div class="legal-orb legal-orb2"></div>
    </div>

    <article class="legal-inner">
      <header class="legal-head">
        <div class="badge-pill"><div class="pulse-dot"></div> LEGAL</div>
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated} · Effective: {effectiveDate}</p>
        <p class="lede">
          By installing or using BotPilot, you agree to these terms. Read them.
          They aren't long.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section>
        <h2>1. Who you're agreeing with</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are between you and <strong>1 MEDIA Studio LLC.</strong>
          ("BotPilot", "we", "us"), a Florida limited liability company.
          Contact: <a href="mailto:email@jonathanprivat.com">email@jonathanprivat.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. What you can use</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>BotPilot for Android</strong> — an on-device engagement assistant for Instagram.</li>
          <li><strong>BotPilot Creator for iOS</strong> — a creator inbox, comment manager, and scheduler that connects to your Instagram Professional account through Meta's official Instagram API.</li>
          <li><strong>botpilot.org</strong> — this website.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Account and eligibility</h2>
        <p>
          You must be at least 13 years old (or the minimum age in your
          jurisdiction). You're responsible for your own Instagram account and
          for keeping your BotPilot account credentials secure if you have
          one. You're responsible for everything that happens under your
          account.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Your responsibilities</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Use BotPilot in compliance with Instagram's terms and Meta's Platform Terms. We won't help you violate them.</li>
          <li>Don't use BotPilot to spam, scrape, harass, defraud, or impersonate.</li>
          <li>Don't use BotPilot to send messages to people who haven't opted in or contacted your account first. Meta's 24-hour conversation window is a hard line; we enforce it inside the iOS app.</li>
          <li>Don't reverse-engineer, decompile, or attempt to extract source code from our software, except where permitted by applicable law.</li>
          <li>Don't run BotPilot against an Instagram account you don't own or have explicit written permission to manage.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Third-party services</h2>
        <p>
          BotPilot interoperates with Meta Platforms, Inc. (Instagram, Facebook
          Login, Meta APIs). Your use of those services is governed by their
          own terms and policies. If Meta restricts or terminates your account,
          we cannot override that.
        </p>
        <p>
          BotPilot for Android uses Android's Accessibility Service to drive
          the real Instagram app's UI. The use of Accessibility is permitted by
          Android for assistive automation, but Instagram's terms restrict
          automated engagement. You're responsible for any consequences to your
          Instagram account that result from running the Android app.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Subscriptions and billing (iOS)</h2>
        <p>
          BotPilot Creator may be offered as a paid subscription via in-app
          purchase (Apple) or web-billing (Stripe). Subscriptions auto-renew at
          the price posted on the day you subscribed. You can cancel anytime
          in your App Store account settings or via the subscription
          management page if you bought through web-billing. Refunds follow
          Apple's or Stripe's policy, as applicable.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>
          You may not use BotPilot to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Send unsolicited bulk messages, spam, or commercial messages outside Meta's allowed messaging windows.</li>
          <li>Operate "growth" or "follower farm" schemes that violate Instagram's terms or Meta's Platform Terms.</li>
          <li>Harvest data about Instagram users beyond what Meta authorizes for your use case.</li>
          <li>Run unauthorized automation on Instagram accounts you do not own.</li>
          <li>Build a competing service from our software, branding, or content.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Violations may result in immediate suspension of your access and, in
          serious cases, reporting to Meta or law enforcement.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Our license to you</h2>
        <p>
          We grant you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable,
          revocable license to install and use BotPilot on devices you own or
          control, solely for personal or internal business use. We retain all
          intellectual property in BotPilot itself.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>
          BotPilot is provided "as is" and "as available". To the maximum
          extent permitted by law, we disclaim all warranties, express or
          implied, including merchantability, fitness for a particular
          purpose, and non-infringement. We make no warranty that BotPilot
          will be uninterrupted, error-free, secure, or that any defects will
          be corrected.
        </p>
        <p>
          We are not affiliated with Meta Platforms, Inc., Instagram, or
          Facebook. All trademarks are property of their respective owners.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, BotPilot and its officers,
          directors, employees, and affiliates will not be liable for any
          indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages,
          or for any loss of profits, revenues, data, use, or goodwill,
          arising from or related to your use of BotPilot.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our aggregate liability for any claim arising from or related to
          these Terms will not exceed the greater of (a) US $100 or (b) the
          amount you paid us in the 12 months preceding the claim.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>11. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>
          You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless BotPilot from any
          claims, damages, losses, and expenses (including reasonable
          attorneys' fees) arising from your use of BotPilot in violation of
          these Terms or applicable law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>12. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          You can stop using BotPilot anytime. We can suspend or terminate
          your access if you violate these Terms, if required by law, or if
          continued operation isn't feasible (e.g., Meta revokes platform
          access). On termination we will delete your data per our
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>13. Governing law and disputes</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Florida,
          without regard to conflict-of-laws principles. The exclusive venue
          for any dispute is the state and federal courts located in
          Miami-Dade County, Florida, and you consent to personal jurisdiction
          there. Nothing in this section limits your right to bring a small
          claims action in your local jurisdiction where permitted.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>14. Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms when our products or laws change. The
          "Last updated" date reflects the most recent revision. For material
          changes we will notify you in the app or by email at least 7 days
          before the change takes effect. Continued use after the effective
          date constitutes acceptance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>15. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions or notices:
          <a href="mailto:email@jonathanprivat.com">email@jonathanprivat.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.legal {
  position: relative;
  padding: 120px 24px 80px;
  min-height: 100vh;
  overflow: hidden;
}
.legal-bg {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  z-index: 0;
  pointer-events: none;
}
.legal-orb {
  position: absolute;
  width: 600px;
  height: 600px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  filter: blur(120px);
}
.legal-orb1 {
  top: -200px;
  right: -150px;
  background: var(--orb1);
  animation: float1 24s ease-in-out infinite;
}
.legal-orb2 {
  bottom: -200px;
  left: -150px;
  background: var(--orb2);
  animation: float2 28s ease-in-out infinite;
}
.legal-inner {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 1;
  max-width: 760px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
.legal-head {
  margin-bottom: 48px;
}
.legal-head h1 {
  font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 56px);
  font-weight: 800;
  letter-spacing: -1.5px;
  margin: 20px 0 12px;
  line-height: 1.05;
}
.legal-head .meta {
  color: var(--text-m);
  font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
  font-size: 12px;
  letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  margin-bottom: 24px;
}
.legal-head .lede {
  color: var(--text-m);
  font-size: 17px;
  line-height: 1.55;
  max-width: 600px;
}
.badge-pill {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 8px;
  padding: 6px 14px;
  border-radius: 999px;
  background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--green) 10%, transparent);
  color: var(--green);
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 1.5px;
}
.pulse-dot {
  width: 6px;
  height: 6px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: var(--green);
  box-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--green);
  position: relative;
}
.pulse-dot::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  inset: -3px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: var(--green);
  opacity: 0.4;
  animation: pulseRing 1.8s ease-out infinite;
}
.legal section {
  margin-bottom: 36px;
}
.legal h2 {
  font-size: 22px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.4px;
  margin-bottom: 14px;
  color: var(--text);
}
.legal h3 {
  font-size: 16px;
  font-weight: 700;
  margin: 18px 0 10px;
  color: var(--text);
}
.legal p,
.legal li {
  color: var(--text-m);
  font-size: 15px;
  line-height: 1.65;
  margin-bottom: 12px;
}
.legal p strong,
.legal li strong {
  color: var(--text);
  font-weight: 600;
}
.legal ul {
  padding-left: 22px;
  margin-bottom: 12px;
}
.legal li {
  margin-bottom: 8px;
}
.legal a {
  color: var(--green);
  border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--green) 30%, transparent);
  transition: border-color 0.3s;
}
.legal a:hover {
  border-bottom-color: var(--green);
}
.legal code {
  font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
  font-size: 13px;
  padding: 2px 6px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  background: var(--card);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  color: var(--text);
}
@media (max-width: 639px) {
  .legal {
    padding: 96px 18px 60px;
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-size: 19px;
  }
  .legal p,
  .legal li {
    font-size: 14.5px;
  }
}
</style>
